Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Euler curvature", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.980794977128948*^9, 
  3.980794979122061*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"47de09ed-6963-9243-b04a-\
d70e3c42bee1"],

Cell["\<\
This should be zero. While the eigenstates changes throughout the BZ (i.e. \
the basis vectors at each k is different), they span the same Hilbert space. \
Euler curvature (I believe) measures how twisted the spanned space is.
I think you can think of \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]you need at least three bands \
to see nontrivial Euler class\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] as the embedding of a \
twisted strip in 3D.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.980794988972542*^9, 
  3.9807951839361477`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8f035359-85db-df4f-a945-\
36f5d1545d4e"],

